---
layout: base.njk
title: Showcase
description: "Sites built with retrostrap, a wall of 88×31 buttons, because that is how the web used to say we exist."
---
<h1>Showcase</h1>

<p>Sites built with retrostrap, shown the way the old web showed off: a wall of
88×31 buttons. Because that is how a page used to say <em>we exist</em>.</p>

{% if showcase.length %}
<div class="rs-badge-wall">
  {%- for site in showcase %}
  <a class="rs-button88" href="{{ site.url }}" title="{{ site.title }}, by {{ site.author }}">
    {%- if site.button88 %}<img src="/assets/showcase/{{ site.button88 }}" alt="{{ site.title }}" width="88" height="31">
    {%- else %}{{ site.title }}{% endif %}
  </a>
  {%- endfor %}
</div>
{% else %}
<div class="rs-panel">
  <h2 class="rs-panel__title">The wall is empty, for now</h2>
  <p>No sites yet. <strong>Be the first</strong>, post #1 always gets remembered.
  Build something, wear the badge, and send it in.</p>
</div>
{% endif %}

<hr class="rs-hr rs-hr--rainbow">

<h2>Submit your site</h2>
<p>Open a pull request that adds one entry to
<code>site/data/showcase.json</code> and drops an 88×31 button into
<code>site/assets/showcase/</code>:</p>

<div class="rs-dos">
<span class="rs-dos__title">site/data/showcase.json</span>
<pre>{
  "url": "https://gardengnome.example",
  "title": "The Garden Gnome Registry",
  "author": "gnomekeeper",
  "button88": "gnome-registry.png",
  "added": "2026-06-05"
}</pre>
</div>

<h3>House rules</h3>
<ul class="rs-list rs-list--stars">
  <li>Your site visibly uses retrostrap (a dist link, or an honest fork).</li>
  <li>It passes the Laws, most of all Decency: no tracking, no ads in a trenchcoat.</li>
  <li>Family-friendly; a fifteen-year-old building their first page reads this wall.</li>
  <li>Original button art, no real-brand imitations. The
      <a href="/demos/button-maker/">button-maker</a> will happily make you one.</li>
</ul>

<p class="rs-font-1">Or use the
<a href="https://github.com/retrostrap/retrostrap/issues/new?template=showcase.yml">showcase issue form</a>
and we'll open the PR for you.</p>
